25|$|Exokernels are a still-experimental {{approach}} to operating system design. They {{differ from the}} other types of kernels in that their functionality {{is limited to the}} protection and multiplexing of the raw <b>hardware,</b> providing no <b>hardware</b> abstractions on top of which to develop applications. This separation of <b>hardware</b> protection from <b>hardware</b> management enables application developers to determine how to make the most efficient use of the available <b>hardware</b> for each specific program.|$|E
